title: For Sale:  Minty Yugo M24/47
postcontent: The rifle is in fantastic condition. Bore is mirror like with no pits or frost. Receiver, bolt and the floor plate are matching but the stock and the trigger guard are not.The final additions to the M24 family were thw M24/47 and M24/52 rifles. Both were produced by reworking exiating prewar Serbian Model 24 Mausers and then refurbished with newer Belgian parts during World War II at the Zastava arms (formerly Kragujevac Arsenal) plant, which was at that time under the control of the postwar communist government. "47 and "52" indicate the beginning of the rebuild program for each respective model: 1947 for the M24/47 and 1952 for the M24/52. One common misconception is that the M24/47 rifles were produced on in 1947; actually, the rebuild program lasted into the early 1950s along sidenew production of M48 rifles.Minor cosmetic differences exist between the M24/47 and M24/52, but the rifles are nearly identical to one another and to the M48.You will be pleased, especially at only $340.
